author: Dave Andersen, Northeast Ohio Media Group
title: Video: 'It's an execution league' - Cleveland Browns Berea report
text:
BEREA, Ohio -- Cleveland Browns beat writers Mary Kay Cabot and Tom Reed take a look what happened in Berea as the team continues preparations to play the Baltimore Ravens at M&T Bank Stadium.
Topics include:
Jim O'Neil said that it is an 'execution league' when when talking about the defensive scheme, even though defensively are last in the league. Coaches and players have to execute he said. Danny Shelton was challenged by O'Neil to play better. They would like more explosion from him. Justine Gilbert will be the main kick returner and could even see action in the near future i n some trick plays on offense. Special teams coordinator Chris Tabor watched the offside by Tramon Williams in the Chargers game frame by frame and did not think he jumped. Running back Duke Johnson established himself last Sunday with a big day in the passing game. Safety Tashaun Gipson will most likely be out Sunday against the Ravens with an ankle.
